artist_info.name: Taylor Swift
artist_info.label: Big Machine Records, Republic Records
artist_info.description: Taylor Swift is an American singer-songwriter whose discography spans various genres. Swift is known for her narrative songwriting which often centers around her personal life and has received widespread media coverage and critical praise. She has garnered numerous awards including 11 Grammy Awards. Swift began her career in country music but transitioned into pop and pop rock, making her one of the best-selling music artists of all time.

artist_info.name: Rich Brian
artist_info.label: 88rising, Empire
artist_info.description: Rich Brian, formerly known as Rich Chigga, is an Indonesian rapper, singer, songwriter, and record producer. He gained fame through his viral debut single 'Dat $tick,' which was released in 2016. Brian is part of the Asian music collective 88rising, which promotes Asian artists in the Western music industry. His music incorporates elements of trap, electronic, and hip hop, and is known for its unique blend of humor and self-reflection. Brian has been praised for breaking stereotypes and paving the way for more Asian artists in the predominantly Western-dominated music industry.

artist_info.description: Taylor Swift is an American singer-songwriter renowned for her versatile music style, seamlessly transitioning between country, pop, and pop rock. Her songwriting, often inspired by her personal experiences, has garnered critical acclaim and a massive fan following worldwide. Swift's impact on music is highlighted by her numerous awards, including 11 Grammy Awards. She is celebrated for her storytelling in songs, which has resonated with a global audience, making her one of the most influential artists of her generation.
